## [Standard ASP.NET Core and Node.js ignore patterns]

# --- .NET / Visual Studio ---
bin/
obj/
[Xx][Bb][Ii][Nn]/
[Zz][Oo][Bb][Jj]/
_ReSharper*/
*.[Rr]e[Ss]harper
*.user
*.userosscache
*.sln.docuser
.vs/
.vscode/
*.suo
*.userprefs
*.btp
*.ide
*.orig
*.suo
*.user
*.userosscache

# --- Node.js ---
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
.pnpm-debug.log*
package-lock.json
bun.lockb

# --- Frontend Build Artifacts ---
# We keep output.css as it is needed for the site to run without Node
# but you can ignore it if your build server generates it
# wwwroot/css/output.css

# --- Environment Secrets ---
.env
.env.development
.env.production
.env.local
# Note: appsettings.json is often kept for structure, but secrets should be in User Secrets or Environment Variables

# --- OS Specific ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
